{
  "document_id": "lam-3",
  "title": "Lamentations 3",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "I am one who has seen affliction"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "he has driven and brought me"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "against me alone he turns his hand,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "He has made my flesh and my skin waste away;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "he has besieged and enveloped me"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "he has made me sit in darkness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "He has walled me about so that I cannot escape;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "though I call and cry for help,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "he has blocked my ways with hewn stones;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "He is a bear lying in wait for me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "he led me off my way and tore me to pieces;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "he bent his bow and set me"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "He shot into my vitals"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "I have become the laughingstock of all my people,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "He has filled me with bitterness;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "He has made my teeth grind on gravel;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "my soul is bereft of peace;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "so I say, “Gone is my glory"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "The thought of my affliction and my homelessness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "My soul continually thinks of it"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "But this I call to mind,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "The steadfast love of the Lord never ceases,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "they are new every morning;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "“The Lord is my portion,” says my soul,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "The Lord is good to those who wait for him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "It is good that one should wait quietly"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "It is good for one to bear"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "to sit alone in silence"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "to put one’s mouth to the dust"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "to give one’s cheek to the smiter"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "For the Lord will not"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "Although he causes grief, he will have compassion"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "for he does not willingly afflict"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "When all the prisoners of the land"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "when justice is perverted"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "when one’s case is subverted—"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "Who can command and have it done,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "Is it not from the mouth of the Most High"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-39",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 39,
      "text": "Why should any who draw breath complain"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-40",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 40,
      "text": "Let us test and examine our ways"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-41",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 41,
      "text": "Let us lift up our hearts as well as our hands"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-42",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 42,
      "text": "We have transgressed and rebelled,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-43",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 43,
      "text": "You have wrapped yourself with anger and pursued us,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-44",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 44,
      "text": "you have wrapped yourself with a cloud"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-45",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 45,
      "text": "You have made us filth and rubbish"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-46",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 46,
      "text": "All our enemies"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-47",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 47,
      "text": "panic and pitfall have come upon us,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-48",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 48,
      "text": "My eyes flow with rivers of tears"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-49",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 49,
      "text": "My eyes will flow without ceasing,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-50",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 50,
      "text": "until the Lord from heaven"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-51",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 51,
      "text": "My eyes cause me grief"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-52",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 52,
      "text": "Those who were my enemies without cause"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-53",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 53,
      "text": "they flung me alive into a pit"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-54",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 54,
      "text": "water closed over my head;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-55",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 55,
      "text": "I called on your name, O Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-56",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 56,
      "text": "you heard my plea, “Do not close your ear"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-57",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 57,
      "text": "You came near when I called on you;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-58",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 58,
      "text": "You have taken up my cause, O Lord;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-59",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 59,
      "text": "You have seen the wrong done to me, O Lord;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-60",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 60,
      "text": "You have seen all their malice,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-61",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 61,
      "text": "You have heard their taunts, O Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-62",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 62,
      "text": "The whispers and murmurs of my assailants"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-63",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 63,
      "text": "Whether they sit or rise—see,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-64",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 64,
      "text": "Pay them back for their deeds, O Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-65",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 65,
      "text": "Give them anguish of heart;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "lam-3-66",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 66,
      "text": "Pursue them in anger and destroy them"
    }
  ]
}